On Friday, the White House held a roundtable discussion with over 20 leaders from the entertainment industry to talk about including accurate mental health storylines in film and series content. The meeting was part of President Biden's commitment to addressing the mental health crisis in the country. The participants discussed the actions President Biden has taken so far to strengthen the mental health workforce, improve access to care, and create supportive environments. They also talked about opportunities for proactive mental health storylines, lessons learned from previous campaigns, and how to sensitively depict mental health challenges. The participants agreed to continue the conversation and work together to decrease stigma and promote access to mental health resources.